The paper proposes a framework for collaborative deep reinforcement learning, which involves knowledge transfer among heterogeneous learning agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
